title: Fernhill D5 — the boiler's three-stage startup, order enforced
story: fernhill
description: The `define machine` flagship — FILL, PRIME, LIGHT, in that
  order. Out-of-order attempts are rejected with their own voices (the dry
  primer, the clanking cold light); each legal transition mirrors onto the
  boiler's visible states and speaks its on-enter line.
---

> north
[OK: contains "Gravel Drive"]

> north
[OK: contains "Fountain Court"]

> east
[OK: contains "old coal dust"]

# Out of order: prime before filling — the dry wheeze
> push the primer
[OK: contains "Nothing to prime"]

# Out of order: light before priming — the clank
> turn on the boiler
[OK: contains "hollow CLANK"]

# FILL
> turn the stopcock
[OK: contains "You crank the stopcock"]
[OK: contains "water gurgles"]

# Still can't light: primed is the gate, filled is not enough
> turn on the boiler
[OK: contains "hollow CLANK"]

# PRIME
> push the primer
[OK: contains "thumps home"]

# LIGHT
> turn on the boiler
[OK: contains "warmth crawls toward the greenhouse"]

# The machine's terminal state is mirrored onto the entity's states —
# and the A5 frost seal reads the switchable flank of the same beat
> examine the boiler
[OK: contains "FILL. PRIME. LIGHT."]
